 in JSTOR]\n* Weinberg, Gerhard L. ''Visions of Victory: The Hopes of Eight World War II Leaders.'' (2005). 292 pp. chapter on de Gaulle\n\n===Politics===\n* Berstein, Serge, and Peter Morris. ''The Republic of de Gaulle 1958\u20131969'' (The Cambridge History of Modern France) (2006) [https://www.amazon.com/Republic-Gaulle-1958-1969-Cambridge-History/dp/0521272394/ref=sr_1_7?ie=UTF8&s=books&qid=1205076945&sr=1-7 excerpt and text search]\n* Cameron, David R. and Hofferbert, Richard I. \"Continuity and Change in Gaullism: the General's Legacy.\" ''American Journal of Political Science'' 1973 17(1): 77\u201398. {{ISSN|0092\u20135853}}, a statistical analysis of the Gaullist voting coalition in elections 1958\u201373 Fulltext: [https://www.jstor.org/stable/2110475 Abstract in Jstor]\n* Cogan, Charles G. \"The Break-up: General de Gaulle's Separation from Power,\" ''Journal of Contemporary History'' Vol. 27, No. 1 (Jan. 1992), pp.&nbsp;167\u2013199, re: 1969 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/260783 in JSTOR]\n* Diamond, Robert A. ''France under de Gaulle'' (Facts on File, 1970), highly detailed chronology 1958\u20131969.  319pp \n* Furniss, Edgar J., Jr. ''De Gaulle and the French Army.'' (1964)\n* Gough, Hugh and Horne, John, eds. ''De Gaulle and Twentieth-Century France.'' (1994). 158 pp. essays by experts\n* Hauss, Charles. ''Politics in Gaullist France: Coping with Chaos'' (1991) [https://www.questia.com/read/23380015 online edition]\n* Hoffmann, Stanley. ''Decline or Renewal? France since the 1930s'' (1974) [https://www.questia.com/read/14783192 online edition]\n* Jackson, Julian. \"General de Gaulle and His Enemies: Anti-Gaullism in France Since 1940,\" ''Transactions of the Royal Historical Society'' 6th Ser., Vol. 9 (1999), pp.&nbsp;43\u201365 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/3679392 in JSTOR]\n* Merom, Gil. \"A 'Grand Design'? Charles de Gaulle and the End of the Algerian War,\" ''Armed Forces & Society''(1999) 25#2 pp: 267\u2013287 [http://afs.sagepub.com/content/25/2/267.short online ]\n* Nester, William R. ''De Gaulle's Legacy: The Art of Power in France's Fifth Republic'' (Palgrave Macmillan, 2014)\n* Northcutt, Wayne. ''Historical Dictionary of the French Fourth and Fifth Republics, 1946\u20131991'' (1992)\n* Pierce, Roy, \"De Gaulle and the RPF\u2014A Post-Mortem,\" ''The Journal of Politics'' Vol. 16, No. 1 (Feb. 1954), pp.&nbsp;96\u2013119 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/2126340 in JSTOR]\n* Rioux, Jean-Pierre, and Godfrey Rogers. ''The Fourth Republic, 1944\u20131958'' (The Cambridge History of Modern France) (1989)\n* Shepard, Todd. ''The Invention of Decolonization: The Algerian War and the Remaking of France.'' (2006). 288 pp.\n* Williams, Philip M. and Martin Harrison. ''De Gaulle's Republic'' (1965) [https://www.questia.com/read/54328775 online edition]\n\n===Foreign policy===\n{{Main|Foreign policy of Charles de Gaulle#Further reading}}\n* Bozo, Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric. ''Two Strategies for Europe: De Gaulle, the United States and the Atlantic Alliance'' (2000)\n* Gordon, Philip H. ''A Certain Idea of France: French Security Policy and the Gaullist Legacy'' (1993) [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=107405557 online edition]\n* Grosser, Alfred. ''French foreign policy under De Gaulle'' (Greenwood Press, 1977)\n* Kolodziej, Edward A. ''French International Policy under de Gaulle and Pompidou: The Politics of Grandeur'' (1974) [https://www.questia.com/read/9120986 online edition]\n* Kulski, W. W. ''De Gaulle and the World: The Foreign Policy of the Fifth French Republic'' (1966) [https://archive.org/details/degaulleworld00kuls online free to borrow]\n* Logevall, Fredrik. \"De Gaulle, Neutralization, and American Involvement in Vietnam, 1963\u20131964,\" ''The Pacific Historical Review'' Vol. 61, No. 1 (Feb. 1992), pp.&nbsp;69\u2013102 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/3640789 in JSTOR]\n* Mahan, E. ''Kennedy, De Gaulle and Western Europe.'' (2002). 229 pp.\n* Mangold, Peter. ''The Almost Impossible Ally: Harold Macmillan and Charles de Gaulle.'' (2006). 275 pp.&nbsp;IB Tauris, London, {{ISBN|978-1-85043-800-7}}\n* Martin, Garret Joseph. ''General de Gaulle's Cold War: Challenging American Hegemony, 1963\u20131968'' (Berghahn Books; 2013) 272 pages\n* Moravcsik, Andrew. \"Charles de Gaulle and Europe: The New Revisionism.\" ''Journal of Cold War Studies'' (2012) 14#1 pp: 53\u201377.\n* Nuenlist, Christian. ''Globalizing de Gaulle: International Perspectives on French Foreign Policies, 1958\u20131969'' (2010)\n* Newhouse, John. ''De Gaulle and the Anglo-Saxons'' (New York: Viking Press, 1970)\n* Paxton, Robert O. and Wahl, Nicholas, eds. ''De Gaulle and the United States: A Centennial Reassessment.'' (1994). 433 pp.\n* White, Dorothy Shipley. ''Black Africa and de Gaulle: From the French Empire to Independence.'' (1979). 314 pp.\n\n===Ideas and memory===\n* Cerny, Philip G. ''The Politics of Grandeur: Ideological Aspects of de Gaulle's Foreign Policy.'' (1980). 319 pp.\n* Clague, Monique. \"Conceptions of Leadership: Charles de Gaulle and Max Weber,\" ''Political Theory'' (1975) 3#4 pp.&nbsp;423\u2013440 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/190838 in JSTOR]\n* Converse, Philip E., et al. ''De Gaulle and Eisenhower: The public image of the victorious general'' (1961), Statistical analysis of public opinion polls in US and France\n* Hazareesingh, Sudhir. ''In the Shadow of the General: Modern France and the Myth of De Gaulle'' (2012) [http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showpdf.php?id=36448 online review]\n* Hoffmann, Stanley. \"The Hero as History: De Gaulle's War Memoirs\" in Hoffman ''Decline or Renewal? France since the 1930s'' (1974) pp 187\u2013201 [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=14783192# online edition]\n* Johnson, Douglas. \"The Political Principles of General de Gaulle,\" ''International Affairs'' (1965) 41#4 pp.&nbsp;650\u2013662 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/2610718 in JSTOR]\n* Mahoney, Daniel J. ''De Gaulle: Statesmanship, Grandeur, and Modern Democracy.'' (1996). 188 pp. intellectual history\n* Mahoney, Daniel J. \"A 'Man of Character': The Statesmanship of Charles de Gaulle,\" ''Polity'' (1994) 27#1 pp.&nbsp;157\u2013173 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/3235090 in JSTOR]\n* Morrisey, Will. \"Reflections on De Gaulle: Political Founding in Modernity.\" (2002). 266 pp. intellectual history\n* Pedley, Alan. ''As Mighty as the Sword: A Study of the Writings of Charles de Gaulle'' (1996) 226pp\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links|wikt=no|v=no|n=no|voy=no}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110128132924/http://www.charles-de-gaulle.org/ Fondation Charles-de-Gaulle]\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Charles de Gaulle |sopt=t}}\n* {{worldcat id|id=lccn-n79-41762}}\n* [http://www.memorial-charlesdegaulle.fr/en/index.html M\u00e9morial Charles de Gaulle]\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/005897}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Offices and distinctions\n|list1=\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-new|office|rows=3}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Leader of [[Free France]]|years=1940\u20131943}}\n{{s-non|reason=Office abolished|rows=3}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-ttl|title=President of the [[French National Committee]]|years=1941\u20131943}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-ttl|title=President of the [[French Committee of National Liberation]]|years=1943\u20131944|alongside=[[Henri Giraud]]}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before={{ill|Hippolyte Ducos|fr}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Under-Secretary of State for War and National Defence|years=1940}}\n{{s-non|reason=Office abolished}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Philippe P\u00e9tain]]|as=Chief of the [[Vichy France|French State]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chair of the [[Provisional Government of the French Republic|Provisional Government of France]]|years=1944\u20131946|rows=2}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[F\u00e9lix Gouin]]|rows=2}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Pierre Laval]]|as=Chief of the [[Vichy France|Government]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Pierre Pflimlin]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Prime Minister of France]]|years=1958\u20131959}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Michel Debr\u00e9]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Pierre de Chevign\u00e9]]}}\n{{s-ttl|