ombardi199407\">{{Cite magazine |last=Lombardi |first=Chris |date=July 1994 |title=To Hell and Back Again |url=http://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/index.php?year=1994&pub=2&id=120 |magazine=Computer Gaming World |issue=120 |pages=20\u201324 |issn=0744-6667}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MOD105112\">''Masters of Doom'', pp. 105\u2013112</ref>\n<ref name=\"TE5GameUltra\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/blogs/DavidLightbown/20170223/289955/Classic_Tools_Retrospective_John_Romero_talks_about_creating_TEd_the_tile_editor_that_shipped_over_30_games.php |title=Classic Tools Retrospective: John Romero talks about creating TEd, the tile editor that shipped over 30 games |last=Lightbown |first=David |date=2017-02-23 |website=[[Gamasutra]] |publisher=[[UBM plc|UBM]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701072739/http://www.gamasutra.com/blogs/DavidLightbown/20170223/289955/Classic_Tools_Retrospective_John_Romero_talks_about_creating_TEd_the_tile_editor_that_shipped_over_30_games.php |archive-date=2017-07-01 |access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MOD113117\">''Masters of Doom'', pp. 113\u2013117</ref>\n<ref name=\"Gamasutra-CKTech\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/344672/How_id_built_Wolfenstein_3D_using_Commander_Keen_tech.php |title=How id built Wolfenstein 3D using Commander Keen tech |last=Sanglard |first=Fabien |date=June 24, 2019 |website=[[Gamasutra]]}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NeXT-Wolf3D\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.mt/books?id=_H8lAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA188 |title=The Technical and Social History of Software Engineering |last=Jones |first=Capers |date=2013-11-12 |publisher=[[Addison-Wesley]] |isbn=978-0321903426 |page=188}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Pacman\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.joystiq.com/2012/03/09/these-games-inspired-cliff-bleszinski-john-romero-will-wright/ |title=These games inspired Cliff Bleszinski, John Romero, Will Wright, and Sid Meier |last=Bailey |first=Kat |date=2012-03-09 |website=Joystiq |publisher=[[AOL]]