 3D Noah's Ark Came to Be Reprinted on SNES in 2014 |last=Matulef |first=Jeffrey |date=2014-01-24 |website=[[Eurogamer]] |publisher=Gamer Network |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304053535/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2014-01-22-how-super-3d-noahs-ark-came-to-be-reprinted-on-snes-in-2014 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |access-date=2015-06-14}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"ENGINErott\">{{Cite web|url=http://legacy.3drealms.com/rott/originalspec.html |title=ROTT Original Design Spec |publisher=[[3D Realms]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815142753/http://legacy.3drealms.com/rott/originalspec.html |archive-date=2016-08-15 |access-date=2011-05-10}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Apogee FAQ Softdisk\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rinkworks.com/apogee/s/2.7.2.shtml |title=The Apogee FAQ: What's Apogee's relationship with Softdisk? |last=Stoddard |first=Samuel |website=The Apogee FAQ |publisher=Samuel Stoddard |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313202627/http://rinkworks.com/apogee/s/2.7.2.shtml |archive-date=2016-03-13 |access-date=2016-07-28}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MOD166\">''Masters of Doom'', p. 166</ref>\n<ref name=\"OW\">''Online Worlds'', p. 21</ref>\n<ref name=\"ROTThistory\">{{Cite web|url=http://rott.classicgaming.gamespy.com/hell/ |title=ROTT in Hell |last=Bowen |first=Kevin |date=July 1997 |website=[[GameSpy|Planet Quake]] |publisher=[[Mark Surfas]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090421053341/http://rott.classicgaming.gamespy.com/hell/ |archive-date=2009-04-21 |access-date=2016-08-23}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"RTCW\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/r_rtcw |title=Return to Castle Wolfenstein |last=Bramwell |first=Tom |date=2001-12-21 |website=[[Eurogamer]] |publisher=Gamer Network |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304080455/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/r_rtcw |archive-date=2016-03-04 |access-date=2016-07-28}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"WTNC\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/wolfenstein-2-the-new-colossus-review/ |title=Wolfenstein 2: The New Colossus review |last=Roberts |first=Samuel |date=2017-10-26 |website=[[PC Gamer]] |publisher=[[Future plc]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027102006/http://www.pcgamer.com/wolfenstein-2-the-new-colossus-review/ |archive-date=2017-10-27 |access-date=2017-10-27}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{Cite book|title=[[Masters of Doom|Masters of Doom: How Two Guys Created an Empire and Transformed Pop Culture]] |last=Kushner |first=David |date=2004 |publisher=[[Random House]] |isbn=978-0-8129-7215-3}}\n* {{Cite book|title=Online Worlds: Convergence of the Real and the Virtual |date=2009 |publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer Verlag]] |isbn=978-1-84882-824-7 |editor-last=Bainbridge |editor-first=William Sims |editor-link=William Sims Bainbridge}}\n* {{Cite book|title=Doom: Scarydarkfast |last=Pinchbeck |first=Dan |date=2013 |publisher=[[University of Michigan Press]] |isbn=978-0-472-05191-5}}\n* {{Cite book|title=The Ultimate History of Video Games |last=Kent |first=Steven L. |date=2010 |publisher=[[Three Rivers Press]] |isbn=978-0-307-56087-2 |author-link=Steven L. Kent}}\n* {{Cite book|title=The Video Game Explosion |last=Wolf |first=Mark J. P. |date=2008 |publisher=[[Greenwood Press]] |isbn=978-0-313-33868-7}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{moby game|id=/wolfenstein-3d}}\n*[https://github.com/id-Software/wolf3d ''Wolfenstein 3D'' engine source code]\n*{{Internet Archive game|msdos_Wolfenstein_3D_1992}}\n{{Portal bar|1990s|Video games}}\n{{Wolfenstein series}}\n{{Wolfenstein 3D engine games}}\n{{id Software}}\n{{Apogee Games}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wolfenstein 3d}}\n[[Category:1992 video games]]\n[[Category:3D Realms games]]\n[[Category:3DO Interactive Multiplayer games]]\n[[Category:Acorn Archimedes games]]\n[[Category:Activision games]]\n[[Category:Alternate history video games]]\n[[Category:Amiga 120